85
00:05:39,994 --> 00:05:41,061
-It's not going anywhere.

86
00:05:46,327 --> 00:05:47,561
Thanks, by the way.

87
00:05:47,594 --> 00:05:49,061
-Huh?

88
00:05:49,094 --> 00:05:52,161
-You let me make that
arrest tonight, didn't you?

89
00:05:52,194 --> 00:05:53,961
-Uh-- heh heh.

90
00:05:53,994 --> 00:05:55,827
I wasn't about to
ruin your moment.

91
00:05:55,861 --> 00:05:59,594
-Well, I couldn't have done
this without your help, Kotetsu.

92
00:05:59,627 --> 00:06:00,361
-Ah, come on.

93
00:06:00,394 --> 00:06:01,827
That's not true.

94
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:03,894
And anyway, I'm happy for you.

95
00:06:03,927 --> 00:06:06,461
So is Mr. Maverick,
by the looks of him.

96
00:06:06,494 --> 00:06:07,627
You gotta love that guy.

97
00:06:07,661 --> 00:06:10,161
He's like the patron
saint of heroes.

98
00:06:10,194 --> 00:06:11,594
-Yeah.

99
00:06:11,627 --> 00:06:15,027
He's been like a father to me
for as long as I can remember.

100
00:06:15,061 --> 00:06:16,961
-What do you mean?

101
00:06:16,994 --> 00:06:21,994
-Well, Mr. Maverick and my
parents were very good friends.

102
00:06:22,027 --> 00:06:23,461
He would look after
me whenever they

103
00:06:23,494 --> 00:06:24,861
were tied up with
their research.

104
00:06:28,094 --> 00:06:32,061
He was always there for
me, whenever I needed him--

105
00:06:32,094 --> 00:06:35,661
even on that fateful
Christmas Eve, 21 years ago.

106
00:06:43,127 --> 00:06:44,961
-Thank you so much,
Uncle Maverick.

107
00:06:44,994 --> 00:06:46,427
I'll see you real soon, OK?

108
00:06:56,427 --> 00:06:58,994
BARNABY: Moments later,
my parents were killed.

109
00:06:59,027 --> 00:07:00,927
[gunshot]

110
00:07:09,494 --> 00:07:10,927
-It's time to go.

111
00:07:10,961 --> 00:07:14,527
It's all right, you
won't ever be alone, son.

112
00:07:14,561 --> 00:07:17,127
BARNABY: After that,
I was an orphan,

113
00:07:17,161 --> 00:07:20,661
so Mr. Maverick took me in.

114
00:07:20,694 --> 00:07:23,127
-Starting today, this is
going to be your home.

115
00:07:26,061 --> 00:07:28,794
-He raised me like
I was his own son.

116
00:07:28,827 --> 00:07:29,927
-Oh.

117
00:07:29,961 --> 00:07:31,527
-Even when I was
at boarding school,

118
00:07:31,561 --> 00:07:33,927
he was always
looking out for me.

119
00:07:33,961 --> 00:07:37,494
-This bright young man has just
won the approval of the bureau,

120
00:07:37,527 --> 00:07:40,027
so you'll all be seeing
a lot more of him.

121
00:07:40,061 --> 00:07:42,294
Please welcome the city
of Sternbild's newest

122
00:07:42,327 --> 00:07:44,327
hero, Barnaby Brooks, Junior.

123
00:07:44,361 --> 00:07:45,927
BARNABY: And he knew
I was determined

124
00:07:45,961 --> 00:07:48,394
to find my parents'
killer, so he encouraged

125
00:07:48,427 --> 00:07:52,161
me to become a hero, then he
pulled all the right strings.

126
00:07:52,194 --> 00:07:55,794
Without Mr. Maverick, I
wouldn't be here today.

127
00:07:55,827 --> 00:07:57,694
-That's a hell of a story.

128
00:07:57,727 --> 00:08:02,961
-Until now, my only goal in life
has been to avenge my parents.

129
00:08:02,994 --> 00:08:06,161
But after all this time,
I finally have a new one.

130
00:08:06,194 --> 00:08:07,927
-Huh?

131
00:08:07,961 --> 00:08:09,627
-I want the hero
business Maverick

132
00:08:09,661 --> 00:08:11,861
built to be bigger
and better than ever.

133
00:08:11,894 --> 00:08:13,427
I'm going to make
it happen to show

134
00:08:13,461 --> 00:08:17,061
my gratitude for everything
he's done for me over the years.

135
00:08:17,094 --> 00:08:19,127
I guess that you could
say it's my dream.

136
00:08:19,161 --> 00:08:20,027
[chuckling]

137
00:08:20,061 --> 00:08:21,594
-Chasing the dream, huh?

138
00:08:21,627 --> 00:08:23,027
-And what about
yourself, Kotetsu?

139
00:08:23,061 --> 00:08:23,827
-Huh?

140
00:08:23,861 --> 00:08:24,961
-You must have a dream too?

141
00:08:24,994 --> 00:08:27,227
-Uh--

142
00:08:27,261 --> 00:08:28,494
[gasp]

143
00:08:28,527 --> 00:08:32,027
You know, I'm glad you asked,
'cause I do-- a big one.

144
00:08:32,061 --> 00:08:35,227
I want my kid to think
her old man is cool.

145
00:08:35,261 --> 00:08:36,661
-But that's so simple.

146
00:08:36,694 --> 00:08:37,827
-Hey!

147
00:08:37,861 --> 00:08:40,127
