Thanks.

268
00:14:19,421 --> 00:14:22,388
There's just no way
that can be true.

269
00:14:22,421 --> 00:14:24,188
Do you have any proof?

270
00:14:24,221 --> 00:14:25,855
-I recently spoke
with a guy that

271
00:14:25,888 --> 00:14:28,388
was a hero during
Legend's time and he

272
00:14:28,421 --> 00:14:30,488
had no reason to lie to me.

273
00:14:30,521 --> 00:14:31,855
-That's crazy.

274
00:14:31,888 --> 00:14:33,688
Legend set a record that no
one could touch for years, Ben.

275
00:14:33,721 --> 00:14:35,455
A hero like that wouldn't be--

276
00:14:35,488 --> 00:14:36,988
-Trust me, I know how you feel.

277
00:14:37,021 --> 00:14:38,621
When I first found
out, I certainly

278
00:14:38,655 --> 00:14:40,588
didn't want to
believe it either.

279
00:14:40,621 --> 00:14:42,588
Apparently, when his
power started to go,

280
00:14:42,621 --> 00:14:45,455
they began staging the
program on a regular basis.

281
00:14:45,488 --> 00:14:47,788
They'd let the other heroes
do the work rounding up

282
00:14:47,821 --> 00:14:50,255
the criminals and then
give to the actual credit

283
00:14:50,288 --> 00:14:51,955
for making the arrest.

284
00:14:51,988 --> 00:14:53,855
-Are you serious?

285
00:14:53,888 --> 00:14:56,355
-Not only that, they
even went as far

286
00:14:56,388 --> 00:15:00,121
as erasing any arrest records
that made him look bad.

287
00:15:00,155 --> 00:15:02,988
-So that's why there
were no records on Jake.

288
00:15:03,021 --> 00:15:06,055
-With his powers declining,
I guess he had no choice.

289
00:15:06,088 --> 00:15:08,155
Otherwise, it would have
been impossible to remain

290
00:15:08,188 --> 00:15:09,855
at the top.

291
00:15:09,888 --> 00:15:12,521
I'm told that Legend
was torn up about it.

292
00:15:12,555 --> 00:15:16,688
They say he drowned
himself in alcohol.

293
00:15:16,721 --> 00:15:18,821
So, how are you holding up?

294
00:15:18,855 --> 00:15:20,521
You notice any decline
in your powers?

295
00:15:23,188 --> 00:15:25,021
-Yeah, sort of.

296
00:15:25,055 --> 00:15:26,588
-I see.

297
00:15:26,621 --> 00:15:28,788
Look, let me give
you some advice.

298
00:15:28,821 --> 00:15:31,888
You should start thinking
about what to do with your life

299
00:15:31,921 --> 00:15:34,288
before you end up like Legend.

300
00:15:34,321 --> 00:15:37,055
-I don't want to
quit being a hero.

301
00:15:37,088 --> 00:15:38,021
-Hey, come on.

302
00:15:38,055 --> 00:15:39,555
I don't want you
to quit, either.

303
00:15:39,588 --> 00:15:41,421
But you and I both
know you can't

304
00:15:41,455 --> 00:15:42,721
continue this work forever.

305
00:15:45,555 --> 00:15:48,121
Listen, I'm saying
this for your own good.

306
00:15:48,155 --> 00:15:49,255
-I'm not done yet!

307
00:15:55,055 --> 00:15:56,488
[sigh]

308
00:16:03,421 --> 00:16:05,221
-That makes you a hero too.

309
00:16:08,621 --> 00:16:10,121
[chuckling]

310
00:16:29,355 --> 00:16:32,721
-Yuri, if you ever see people
doing wrong in this world,

311
00:16:32,755 --> 00:16:34,455
you mustn't turn a blind eye.

312
00:16:34,488 --> 00:16:36,988
You have to be strong someday
so you can punish evil.

313
00:16:37,021 --> 00:16:38,821
-OK.

314
00:16:38,855 --> 00:16:42,321
-You'll be a chip off
the old block, son.

315
00:16:42,355 --> 00:16:43,588
[gasp]

316
00:16:43,621 --> 00:16:44,655
Why?

317
00:16:44,688 --> 00:16:46,721
Why are my powers slipping away?

318
00:16:46,755 --> 00:16:48,155
-It's going to be
all right, dear.

319
00:16:48,188 --> 00:16:50,321
You've done more than
enough for this city.

320
00:16:50,355 --> 00:16:51,021
-Shut up!

321
00:16:51,055 --> 00:16:52,355
You don't understand!

322
00:16:52,388 --> 00:16:54,421
People are expecting
me to do this.

323
00:16:54,455 --> 00:16:55,788
I can't let it end like this.

324
00:17:00,921 --> 00:17:04,688
What do you know about my
pain, what I go through?

325
00:17:04,721 --> 00:17:07,121
-I can't turn a
blind eye anymore.

326
00:17:07,155 --> 00:17:08,888
I have to be strong,
no matter what.

327
00:17:17,721 --> 00:17:18,188
-You again.

328
00:17:21,455 --> 00:17:24,121
How long are you going
to torment me, father?

329
00:17:24,155 --> 00:17:26,755
-Do you still honestly
believe that striking me down

330
00:17:26,788 --> 00:17:28,321
was the right thing to do?

331
00:17:28,355 --> 00:17:30,888
-Yes, and I continue to
bring evil to justice

332
00:17:30,921 --> 00:17:33,121
every single day.

333
00:17:33,155 --> 00:17:33,621
-Hmph.

334
00:17:41,688 --> 00:17:43,788
WOMAN: Someone help me!

335
00:17:43,821 --> 00:17:44,421
-Huh?

336
00:17:44,455 --> 00:17:45,755
-Somebody, please!

337
00:17:51,221 --> 00:17:52,188
[grunt]

338
00:17:56,488 --> 00:18:00,821
-Now then, time for your
spanking, sweetheart.

339
00:18:00,855 --> 00:18:02,855
-Hey, what do you
think you're doing?

340
00:18:02,888 --> 00:18:03,755
-Eh?

341
00:18:03,788 --> 00:18:05,121
-Please help me.

342
00:18:05,155 --> 00:18:07,288
-And who might you be?

343
00:18:15,221 --> 00:18:17,355
-Tiger, I want you
on the scene, pronto.

344
00:18:17,388 --> 00:18:19,455
KOTETSU: Sorry,
little busy right now.

345
00:18:19,488 --> 00:18:20,988
-Excuse me?

346
00:18:21,021 --> 00:18:22,788
-You're one of them heroes, eh?

347
00:18:22,821 --> 00:18:24,455
-So what if I am?

348
00:18:24,488 --> 00:18:27,455
[chuckling]

349
00:18:27,488 --> 00:18:30,955
[screaming]

350
00:18:37,821 --> 00:18:39,255
[growl]

351
00:18:52,521 --> 00:18:53,455
Uh.

352
00:18:53,488 --> 00:18:53,955
-Hm?

353
00:18:57,421 --> 00:18:58,588
-Uh, hey, folks.

354
00:18:58,621 --> 00:19:00,121
Sorry to interrupt, heh heh.

355
00:19:03,988 --> 00:19:08,155
-The time for your
judgment has arrived.

356
00:19:08,188 --> 00:19:09,588
[sigh]

357
00:19:13,755 --> 00:19:15,121
-Now you didn't
really think you'd

358
00:19:15,155 --> 00:19:17,421
escape from a hero
of justice, did you?

359
00:19:17,455 --> 00:19:17,921
-Ah!

360
00:19:27,421 --> 00:19:28,888
[groan]

361
00:19:32,921 --> 00:19:33,921
-Sorry, buddy.

362
00:19:33,955 --> 00:19:35,688
You're gonna have to
do better than that.

363
00:19:35,721 --> 00:19:36,121
Huh?

364
00:19:41,488 --> 00:19:42,621
-What do you know?

365
00:19:42,655 --> 00:19:45,355
Looks like I'm doing
better already, eh?

366
00:19:45,388 --> 00:19:48,455
[screaming]

367
00:19:48,488 --> 00:19:49,655
[chuckling]

368
00:19:49,688 --> 00:19:50,921
Pathetic.

369
00:19:50,955 --> 00:19:52,421
Don't they have any standards?

370
00:19:52,455 --> 00:19:56,555
How did a weakling like you
become a hero of justice?

371
00:19:56,588 --> 00:19:57,755
[grunt]

372
00:19:57,788 --> 00:20:00,521
You ought to quit
the hero business.

373
00:20:00,555 --> 00:20:02,255
You can't even stop
a normal human.

374
00:20:05,155 --> 00:20:06,788
ANNOUNCER: Barnaby
has successfully

375
00:20:06,821 --> 00:20:11,588
arrested the terrorists and
rescued countless civilians.

376
00:20:11,621 --> 00:20:14,355
-We heroes fight for justice
and the hard-working people

377
00:20:14,388 --> 00:20:16,821
of Sternbild.

378
00:20:16,855 --> 00:20:20,321
[cheering]

379
00:20:32,288 --> 00:20:34,721
-So, how would you
like a little spanking?

380
00:20:34,755 --> 00:20:36,355
-Sounds like fun.

381
00:20:36,388 --> 00:20:38,021
Do I look like I've been bad?

382
00:20:38,055 --> 00:20:39,388
[chuckling]

383
00:20:39,421 --> 00:20:39,888
DANCER: Oh!

384
00:20:39,921 --> 00:20:40,388
Uh--

385
00:20:40,421 --> 00:20:42,321
-Eh?

386
00:20:42,355 --> 00:20:43,288
-Oh!

387
00:20:43,321 --> 00:20:45,255
[screaming]

388
00:20:49,121 --> 00:20:50,888
-What the hell is that?

389
00:20:55,721 --> 00:20:56,988
-Repent, sinner.

390
00:20:57,021 --> 00:20:59,255
Your judgment is at hand.

391
00:20:59,288 --> 00:21:01,288
-You one of those heroes too?

392
00:21:01,321 --> 00:21:02,988
All right, already, I surrender.

393
00:21:03,021 --> 00:21:05,255
You happy?

394
00:21:05,288 --> 00:21:06,555
Just kidding.

395
00:21:06,588 --> 00:21:09,188
Yaa!

396
00:21:09,221 --> 00:21:10,655
Eh, sorry about that.

397
00:21:10,688 --> 00:21:12,755
G-guess my hands
must have slipped.

398
00:21:12,788 --> 00:21:15,255
-The voice of Thanatos
shall release you

399
00:21:15,288 --> 00:21:17,888
from your dark
curse and send you

400
00:21:17,921 --> 00:21:21,655
down the path of
atonement and rebirth.

401
00:21:21,688 --> 00:21:23,888
-Eh, well, I guess
the jig is up.

402
00:21:23,921 --> 00:21:25,455
I know when I'm beat.

403
00:21:25,488 --> 00:21:27,355
All right, pal, I'll
come along quietly.

404
00:21:27,388 --> 00:21:31,088
You happy?

405
00:21:31,121 --> 00:21:31,955
What, are you deaf?

406
00:21:31,988 --> 00:21:34,355
I said I surrender.

407
00:21:34,388 --> 00:21:36,021
Are you out of your mind?

408
00:21:36,055 --> 00:21:38,888
This isn't what the heroes
of justice as supposed to do.

409
00:21:38,921 --> 00:21:41,988
-You made two mistakes,
unfortunately.

410
00:21:42,021 --> 00:21:45,555
First, I'm not a hero.

411
00:21:45,588 --> 00:21:51,555
Second, this is my
idea of justice.

412
00:21:55,219 --> 00:21:57,986
[music - tamaki, "mind game"]

413
00:23:27,452 --> 00:23:29,686
NEWSCASTER: There's a chance
of possible thunderstorms

414
00:23:29,719 --> 00:23:31,786
in the afternoon, so
please take precautions

415
00:23:31,819 --> 00:23:34,752
when you are out and about.

416
00:23:34,786 --> 00:23:38,019
We've just received breaking
news-- serial killer Benoit

417
00:23:38,052 --> 00:23:40,352
Depardieu, also know
as the Lady Killer,

418
00:23:40,386 --> 00:23:42,852
was murdered last night.

419
00:23:42,886 --> 00:23:44,486
Judging from the
scene of the crime

420
00:23:44,519 --> 00:23:46,152
and according to
eyewitness accounts,

421
00:23:46,186 --> 00:23:48,019
he was killed by Lunatic.

422
00:23:48,052 --> 00:23:50,219
At this point, it's
unclear how the heroes

423
00:23:50,252 --> 00:23:52,919
will handle this turn of events.

424
00:23:52,952 --> 00:23:56,719
-You should start thinking
about what to do with your life.

425
00:23:56,752 --> 00:23:59,252
-You ought to quit
the hero business.

426
00:23:59,286 --> 00:24:01,019
You can't even stop
a normal human.

427
00:24:11,252 --> 00:24:13,719
BARNABY: Hi, I'm Barnaby,
the member of Tiger and Bunny

428
00:24:13,752 --> 00:24:15,919
who goes to the
hairstylist twice a month.

429
00:24:15,952 --> 00:24:17,452
Kotetsu went to
visit his family?

430
00:24:17,486 --> 00:24:19,352
Well, I guess he
could use a break.

431
00:24:19,386 --> 00:24:21,219
I hope you get some
good rest, old man.

432
00:24:21,252 --> 00:24:24,452
Next time on "Tiger and Bunny,"
"Blood is Thicker than Water."

433
00:24:24,486 --> 00:24:26,452
See ya.

